TC_01 - ACCEPT FINDINGS AND TICK THE EH CHANGE CHECKBOX

Action	Data	Expected Result
Log in and navigate to Farmer Dashboard. If Agent: select AMS from Agent Tools and select a client.	Valid Advisor / Farmer / Agent credentials. AMS-notified herd from Q70 (SELECT * FROM VWBS_AMS_NOTIFIED_HERD WHERE amn_year=2026 AND amn_round=1 AND amn_notification_type=‘Artificial Surface’ AND ROWNUM<=10). Confirm pre-submit via Q87 (app_mde_code IN 1,2,3). Confirm active via Q93 (bcus_bus_end_date > SYSDATE).	Farmer Dashboard loads with AMS panel visible.
Click Respond to Findings.	-	AMS response screen opens. Red banner: “Actions and/or failure to take action in response to AMS Notifications may impact all area based scheme payments. Please respond below.”
Verify Quick Filter options are present.	-	Filters visible: View All, Action Required.
Verify all column headers are present.	-	Columns present: Red/Green icon (no header), Townland, Parcel/Plot No./Plot Ref., AMS Status, AMS Findings, Accept/Reject Findings?, Claimed Area (ha), Parcel Use, Actions (view map icon).
Verify parcel list content and AMS legend.	-	Only Red R1 parcels listed. AMS Findings column shows Artificial Surface. Red symbol on each row. AMS Legend bottom-left shows Red Non Compliant. View map icon on each row.
Select the parcel confirmed via Q70 and click Select.	Parcel no. from Q70 for test herd.	Side drawer opens. Edit Parcel bolded at top. Townland and Parcel No. shown. Red symbol with message “Missing mandatory information”. Navigation arrows visible at top of side drawer.
Click the Accept radio button under “Do you accept/reject findings?”	-	Accept selected. EH value displayed in side drawer.
Tick the Request change to EH checkbox.	-	Note input field appears below the checkbox.
Click Save without entering a note.	-	Note field enters error state. Edit Map button remains disabled.
Enter a note in the note field.	Any free text.	Note accepted. Edit Map button becomes enabled.
Click Edit Map.	-	Redirected to iSmart map. AMS Feature of Interest visible if Pre-live environment.
Click Draw, select Draft Exclusion, draw over the artificial surface area, click Confirm.	Area covering the artificial surface parcel from Q70.	Exclusion drawn and confirmed on map.
Enter exclusion label and free text note, then click Confirm Changes.	Label text, note text.	Changes confirmed on map.
Click Return to Land Details.	-	Redirected to AMS response screen. Side drawer reopens. Yellow warning: “Please ensure any exclusions drawn are reflected in your claimed area.”
Amend claimed area if required. Verify icons present.	Updated area value if applicable.	Claimed area is editable. Delete icon visible. No scissors or subdivide icon present (subdivide not permitted R1).
Click Save Changes.	-	Green toast: “You have successfully updated details for Parcel No X.”
Close side drawer.	-	Side drawer closes. Parcel row icon changes from red to green.
POST-CONDITION: Run Q85 - SELECT * FROM vwbs_ams_response WHERE lvl_submit_id IS NOT NULL AND amr_year=2026 AND amr_herd_no=:herd_no AND amr_parcel_no=:parcel_no	herd_no and parcel_no from Q70.	POSITIVE CHECK - Row returned in vwbs_ams_response confirming response record was persisted.

